12/08/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder began a two-day official visit to Romania on Thursday (12 August). He will meet with President Ion Iliescu and Prime Minister Adrian Nastase, and attend a bilateral business forum. The German chancellor is also scheduled to visit the grave of his father, who was killed in Ceanu Mare during World War II. On Friday, Schroeder visits neighbouring Bulgaria. (Rompres - 12/08/04; Mediafax - 11/08/04)
